The paper focuses on improving the ability of deep learning for computer vision tasks with few labeled images, which is a common problem in the computer vision field. The paper proposes two methods that incorporate attention mechanisms and past knowledge to improve the Meta learner's performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also involves deep learning techniques and meta-learning algorithms, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which is related to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
